Classes in org.wso2.carbon.repository used by org.wso2.carbon.repository
Activity
          Representation of a activity that has been performed on the repository.
Aspect
          Deprecated. This is been in registry for so long. But as this is not something related to repository this will be eventually moved out from the carbon kernel Aspects are using to associate custom behaviors with resources; Aspects differ from handlers, in that handlers are automatically applied to a resource, whereas, aspects are needed to be invoked manually through user action (e.g. by clicking a button in the user interface).
Association
          Deprecated. 
Collection
          The Collection Interface.
Comment
          Deprecated. This will removed from carbon kernel as this is a social aspect and not part of a pure repository This interface represents a comment that can be added to a resource. A comment is treated a resource itself and it extends the Resource interface.

This interface can be used to add, view or modify existing comments on the repository.
Registry
          This is the "Full" Registry interface.
RegistryService
          This interface can be used to implement an OSGi Service of the Repository.
Resource
          Interface to represent a resource that is stored on the repository.
Tag
          Deprecated. This is a social aspect and should not be in repository. Therefore, will be removed from kernel Represents a tag and its meta-data. Instances of this class is returned from the Registry interface, when tags for a given resource path is queried.
TaggedResourcePath
          Deprecated. This is a social aspect and should not be in repository. Therefore, will be removed from kernel Contains a resource path and tagging details of tags on that resource. Instances of this class is returned from the tag searches. Tag searches may be performed on multiple tags. This class only contains the tag counts for the tags that included in the search. e.g. If the search is for tags java, jsp and programming and if the resource /books/computer/Java Web Development matches the search, counts are only contained for the tags java, jsp and programming although that resource may have many other tags like internet, web, servlets.
TransactionManager
          This describes a an instance of the manager class that can be used to manage transactions on the back-end database.
